9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 19, L.D. 55, “An Act to Amend the Law
10 Governing the Accrual of Earned Paid Leave”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 26 MRSA §637, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 156, §3 and affected by
14 §4, is amended to read:
15 3. Accrual. An employee is entitled to earn one hour of paid leave from a single
16 employer for every 40 hours worked, up to 40 hours in one year of employment. Accrual
17 of leave begins at the start of employment, but the employer is not required to permit use
18 of the leave before the employee has been employed by that employer for 120 days during
19 a one-year period. Accrued and unused hours of earned paid leave from the previous year
20 of employment must be available for use by an employee in the year of employment
21 immediately following the previous year. Accrued and unused hours of earned paid leave
22 carried forward from the previous year of employment may not reduce the total amount of
23 hours of paid leave an employee is entitled to earn in the year of employment immediately
24 following the previous year, up to 40 hours or the accrual limit specified in the employer's
25 policy governing paid leave, whichever is higher. The Department of Labor shall enforce
26 this subsection within existing resources using strategic enforcement.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment replaces the bill and provides that accrued and unused hours of earned
3311 paid leave from the previous year of employment must be available for use by an employee
3322 in the year of employment immediately following the previous year. Accrued and unused
3333 hours of earned paid leave carried forward from the previous year of employment may not
3344 reduce the total amount of hours of paid leave an employee is entitled to earn in the year of
